The effects of Cu2+ concentration (
x 1
), reaction temperature (
x 2
), and residence time (
x 3
) on the fluorescent quantum yield of CDs produced from commercially available OPN leaves powder were assessed within the investigation region using RSM. This approach is more favorable for fine-tuning synthesis reaction conditions (Ferreira et al., 2007). The experimental runs were labeled sequentially as H1 to H15, following the randomized experimental matrix generated by the Statistica® 13.5 software. Table 2 presents the Box-Behnken design, with 15 experiments conducted in a randomized order, along with their corresponding fluorescent quantum yields.
